(thirdQuint)Automated Device for Asthma Monitoring and Management in Monitoring Adult Patients With Lung Cancer Undergoing Radiation Therapy.

 PRIMARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 Determine compliance with the Automated Device for Asthma Monitoring and Management (ADAMM) device in patients receiving radiation therapy (RT) for lung cancer.

 SECONDARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 Evaluate feasibility of recruitment, acceptability of the ADAMM device, and compliance with electronic patient-reported outcomes (ePROs) in this patient population.

